<br>
Let's do the maths shall we?<br>
<br>
assume 20% tax.  Person earning $15,000 will pay $2000 in tax thus having a tax rate of (2000 / 15,000) * 100 or 13.333% whereas the person earning $15,000,000 will have $5,000 untaxed and $14,995,000 taxed at 20% thus (2,999,000 / 15,000,000) * 100 or 19.993% which is a difference effectively creating multiple tax brackets thus making your system progressive.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Once again, playing with words. All you are trying to do is set up a situational justification.  There is no reason or cause to treat the 'rich' worse simply because they have succeeded. I imagine that you would prefer a socialist/communist system where everyone has the same income.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
