<br>
Now the socialist/communist comment does deserve a bit more depth of reply being that it came from a libertarian.  Libertarians tend to have a very narrow view of the world.  They believe in absolutes, they believe that only free market capitalism with as few regulations as possible should be used.  They believe that the environment is something we can destroy at will.  They believe that government shouldn't exist or that if it should it should be so small that it does almost nothing.  They believe that they are right and that no one could ever come up with a better economic system despite the fact that it's already happened.<br>
