<br>
Libertarians tend to have a basic philosophy, and unlike so many others we actually try and abide by it. Yes, we tend to believe in a minimalist government; not a lack of government, but one that does only what is necessary. We understand the need for a government to tax its population in order to fund itself. We fully support the government enforcing laws to prevent actual crimes (those that deprive people of life, liberty, or property by use of force or fraud).<br>
<br>
We do not support the destruction of the environment. That is a blanket statement that is based on a false assumption. We view the environment, and any destruction of the environment, as a property rights issue. Any action that damages the property of others is wrong, and you can be held liable for it.<br>
<br>
As for the mass deforestation in third world countries, again we do not support it – but how are we to stop it? Now that we (the industrialized nations) have climbed to the top of the heap, do we tell everyone else they cannot emulate us? Yea, that will work. We come across as hypocrites. <br>
<br>
Do we support the free market – Yes. No better system exists. Does it need oversight to prevent fraud - Yes. Personally, I feel many of our arcane laws that create Corporations as entities (leaving the board members and stockholders with little or no liability for corporate misdeeds) are wrong and should be changed. It would be a vastly different world if the Ford could be held accountable for the diseases caused by auto pollution (i.e. – the massive increase in asthma). You bet you’re a## we would see cleaner cars. <br>
<br>
Okay, enough of a rant for now. If you don’t like Libertarian philosophy, fine. You think the Cato institute a load of crap, fine; but you should back up your statements with facts. What, specifically do they lie about?<br>
<br>
I think the best argument against Libertarianism is it is somewhat utopian. Libertarians tend to believe that people will play fair, and we all know they wont. But as far a utopian ideals go, Libertarianism is a pretty benign one.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.lp.org/">US Libertarian Party</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
Choice, freedom, trade, respect – god the horror! Make it stop!<br>
