<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> OK. So now that we've gotten to the point at which it has been stated that it won't hurt the economy (although that really doesn't matter all that much) we can get to the effects on people. The rich can afford to lose a bit of extra money while the poor can not. Besides you're in a democracy so whether you like it or not you'll have to cater to the majority. Don't do that you get your head chopped off.<br>
