How about managing the forests so they don't get cut down too quickly?<br>
<br>
Where ever wood can be replaced do so.  Instead of burning wood for heat use electricity from a nuclaer plant (we may as well provide it to them).<br>
<br>
It'll take a lot of time and money to do but if the first world wants to lift the third out of poverty we could do it.  Forget about loans to third world governments.  They'll probably just go to some military there used to oppress the population.  Instead you want to make sure the money goes to the people of the country.  If it's a democracy then it shouldn't be too much of a problem provided it really is a democracy.  No structural adjustments like what the World Bank requires.  They're not really doing any good for the people of the country (those that matter) instead they're just providing companies with a place to do whatever they like.<br>
